English and Buff go on a journey and resort again to their ridiculous tricks: disguised by waiters they commit a fire in a chic French restaurant; then they sow chaos, illegally going abroad on a luxury yacht Volta; English arranges a real mess when trying to take advantage of the shovel.
All stops bring us to the last episode, but with its good-naturedness and madness it is somewhat like a movie for children.
Passing film.
As with the other Johnny English movies, I asked myself the same question: can’t the British film industry offer Rowan Atkinson a role that really fits his talent?
