It’s like using Google Drive, Microsoft Outlook, Slack and Spotify in one browser at a time.
The unique feature of this personal online data repository is that it fully meets the needs of the user, who can access any information.
The company calls it an “expansion of personal capabilities through data.”
According to Inrupt CEO John Bruce, the company aims to leverage resources, processes and related skills to make the Solid platform accessible to everyone.
The company currently consists of Berners-Lee, Bruce, a security platform acquired from IBM, several full-time developers hired to work on the project, and a community of volunteer programmers.
Starting this week, technology developers around the world can create their own standalone apps using the tools available on the Inrupt website.
