Federal prosecutors demand rare death penalty for suspect in New York terror attack
In New York, federal prosecutors are demanding the death penalty for Saifullo Saipov, a suspected terrorist attack in New York that killed eight people – a rare punishment that has not been applied in the state for a federal crime since 1953.
