Up-to-date information about the red tide: decrease in concentration in the districts of Pinellas, Manat and Sarasota
A recent report by the Florida Fish and Wildlife Commission shows a general decline in the level of red-colored microorganisms in parts of Tampa Bay.
According to the Florida Fish and Wildlife Commission, the abundant flowering conditions reported in certain areas of Pinellas, Manat, Sarasota, Charlotte and Collier counties indicate a decrease in concentration.
The flowering of red microorganisms extends about 130 miles of coastline from the north of Pinellas to the southern districts of Lee.
Spots can be found about 10 miles off the coast of Hillsborough County, but fewer than last week.
