Last week, it was reported that there was an average concentration in Pinellas County and in its coastal zone, a low to high concentration in Hillsborough County, a high concentration in Manat County, a high concentration in Sarasota County and in its coastal zone, and an average concentration in Charlotte County and Highland County.
In Pinellas, Manat, Sarasota, Lee and Collier counties continue to report respiratory irritation.
No such reports were reported in northwest Florida last week.
